DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

Context("Numeric");
Context()->strings->add(none => {});

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$d = non_zero_random(-5, 2) + 7;
$n = random(2, 9);

$m = 1;
$k = $d * $n;

BEGIN_PGML
If possible write the following equation in *slope-intercept* form.

    [``` \frac{y-x}{ [$d] } = [$n] ```]

a) What is the value of [` m`] when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter *none* in the box.

    [`m =  `] [_]{Real($m)}

b) What is the value of [`b`] when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter *none* in the box.

    [` b = `] [_]{Real($k)}

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Rewriting in slope-intercept form:
[``` \frac{y-x}{ [$d] } = [$n] ```]
  
[``` y - x = ([$n])([$d]) ```]
  
[``` y = x + [$k] ```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();